description:
Flex defines a default, or Application, container that lets you start adding content to your application without explicitly defining another container.  <p>The Application container has the following default characteristics:</p> <table class=&quot;innertable&quot;> <tr> <th>Characteristic</th> <th>Description</th> </tr> <tr> <td>Default size</td> <td>375 pixels high and 500 pixels wide in the Standalone Flash Player, and all available space in a browser</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Minimum size</td> <td>0 pixels wide and 0 pixels high</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Maximum size</td> <td>No limit</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Default skin class</td> <td>spark.skins.spark.ApplicationSkin</td> </tr> </table>   <p>The <code>&lt;s:Application&gt;</code> tag inherits all of the tag attributes of its superclass and adds the following tag attributes:</p>  <pre>
 &lt;s:Application
 <strong>Properties</strong>
 applicationDPI=<i>Device dependent</i>&quot;
 backgroundColor=&quot;0xFFFFFF&quot;
 colorCorrection=&quot;default&quot;
 controlBarContent=&quot;null&quot;
 controlBarLayout=&quot;HorizontalLayout&quot;
 controlBarVisible=&quot;true&quot;
 frameRate=&quot;24&quot;
 pageTitle&quot;&quot;
 preloader=&quot;<i>No default</i>&quot;
 preloaderChromeColor=&quot;<i>No default</i>&quot;
 resizeForSoftKeyboard=true&quot;
 runtimeDPIProvider=&quot;RuntimeDPIProvider&quot;
 scriptRecursionLimit=&quot;1000&quot;
 scriptTimeLimit=&quot;60&quot;
 splashScreenImage=&quot;&quot;
 splashScreenMinimumDisplayTime=&quot;1000&quot;
 splashScreenScaleMode=&quot;none&quot;
 usePreloader=&quot;true&quot;
 viewSourceURL=&quot;&quot;
 xmlns:<i>No default</i>=&quot;<i>No default</i>&quot;

 <strong>Events</strong>
 applicationComplete=&quot;<i>No default</i>&quot;
 error=&quot;<i>No default</i>&quot;
 /&gt;
 </pre>
